abstract: >-
  Horosa for Windows v2.6.0 beta is a local-first metaphysics workstation that aligns the
  latest Mac-side work (a Liuren "Bi Fa 100" interpretation layer with imagery / casting-guide /
  shen-sha / three-transmission diagrams; a comprehensive Zi Wei Dou Shu P0–P2 enhancement —
  miscellaneous-star display, school-specific four-transformation tables, cascading flow-stars,
  pattern detail and new patterns, Tian-Shang / Tian-Shi — with rebuilt astrostudyboot.jar; a Qi
  Men Dun Jia "Fa Qi Men" (Xun Shuang) overlay for resolution / use-god / imagery; a Western
  astrology build-out across mundane / horary / electional / star-transit with engineering fixes;
  professional city search with traditional/simplified + pinyin matching; and two reported
  Windows fixes — issue #16, DeepSeek deep-thinking (reasoner) multi-turn compatibility, by
  passing through reasoning_content and not sending sampling params to reasoning models plus a
  first-byte-only stream retry and an idle watchdog; and issue #17, the casting time now
  refreshing to the moment of selection instead of app-open time) together with a Windows-only
  installer fix for issue #18 — the NSIS installer now force-terminates a running Horosa and its
  scoped embedded sidecars before an in-place upgrade, so over-the-top upgrades no longer fail
  ("Failed to uninstall old application files") and no longer require a manual uninstall first;
  building on the prior planetarium projection refinements, the seven Western progression
  techniques wired into AI analysis, the astrocartography/ACG map, horary/electional charts,
  the Heluo Lishu completion, AI system-proxy support, the SSE service-stability fix, the global
  day-boundary / late-zi-hour model, the Ed25519-signed in-app auto-update, 数算 methods, the
  harmonic chart, and clean-machine fixes) and AI Analysis rework, astrology modules,
  traditional Chinese methods, kentang/kin backend integrations, AI-assisted structured export,
  Python and Java services, and self-contained Windows desktop delivery into one cross-platform
  release line.

